channel.title: Ideas?
channel.description: I want to ask your guys something. On my way home from the movies all of a sudden I went numb and couple minutes later was throwing up all over myself. I looked for a place to pull over but there wasn't anywhere at the time. I have no idea how I made it home as it is hard to keep your eyes on the road while puking all over yourself. I wasn't drinking at all, completely sober I just started randomly puking all over myself for a few minutes. By the time I got home I was completely fine. Anyone ever had this happen to them or have any ideas as to what caused it?

item.title: Ideas?
item.dc:creator: @R.I.P_RSC R.I.P RSC
item.description:
@R.I.P_RSC wrote:

Related story: I had a fucking panic attack this morning. One of my two major irrational fears is the fear of spraining my ankle. It’s a pretty stupid fear, but I guess that’s the point of an irrational fear. I only get this in the shower, probably because the water gets into my ears and messes with my vestibular system (if that’s even possible), aiding to the fear of somehow spraining my ankle without even moving. So yea, to keep it short, I felt a bit sick in the stomach, and my ankle actually ached (happens quite often because sometimes lie odd while sleeping). While getting the shampoo out of my hair, I lost it. My vision almost completely blacked out (even with my eyes open), and I felt like I was about to fall. I quickly got out, sat down on a stool (with my naked arse!) and let out a nice belch. Felt a bit shaky afterwards, but all was fine.
